<h2>Marketing Automation: The Complete Guide (2026)</h2>
<p>Most businesses spend 15 or more hours each week on repetitive marketing tasks. Sending follow-up emails. Scheduling social posts. Updating spreadsheets. Tracking leads across 4 different platforms.</p>
<p>That time adds up to roughly 780 hours per year. Those are hours you could spend closing deals, improving your product, or building customer relationships.</p>
<p>Marketing automation eliminates that bottleneck. It handles the repetitive work while you focus on strategy and growth. Companies using automation generate <a href="https://thunderbit.com/blog/marketing-automation-statistics">80% more leads</a> and see a 544% return on investment over 3 years.</p>
<p>We publish 3,500+ blogs across 70+ industries and manage <a href="/blog/email-automation-guide/">automated content workflows</a> for businesses of every size. This guide covers everything we know about marketing automation.</p>
<p>Here is what you will learn:</p>
