<p>Roughly one-third of companies automate parts of their content marketing process. This covers blog publishing, content distribution, keyword tracking, performance reporting, and <a href="/blog/content-scoring-guide/">content scoring</a>.</p>
<p>Content automation is where the biggest time savings happen. A single blog post involves research, writing, optimization, formatting, publishing, and distribution. Automating the last 3 steps alone saves 2 to 4 hours per post.</p>
